Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Sought-after 60m2 in the heart of it all

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
A perfectly-sized, approx. 60sqm retail space has become available along Milligan Street, between the busy Hay and Murray Streets at the west end of the Perth CBD.

Surrounded by large office buildings such as QV1, hospitality including The Melbourne Hotel and RAC Arena as well as an abundance of thriving local and national retail, this location presents an exciting opportunity for Food & Beverage, Service and Specialty retail.

With air conditioning, a toilet, hot water and drainage in situ, setting up shop in this tenancy will be a breeze. The tenant here will enjoy huge exposure to heavy passing traffic and high daily footfall.

Don't miss out - book an inspection with the CBRE leasing team today.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HIGH EXPOSURE TENANCY IN THE CITY'S WEST END

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Area of approx 248 sqm on the same level as St Georges Terrace.

Ex banking chamber.

Opportunities for significant company signage on the Terrace. 

Lessor has preference for non food operator as coffee shop already located in the building.

218 is a 7 upper level office building with 20 on-site car parking spaces with rear access from Hay Street. Typical full floor of approximately 640 sqm. 

Building upgrade in 2014 including new lifts, refurbished wet areas and a $1.2m upgrade of the air conditioning. Planned new end of trip facility to be installed.

Please contact Andrew Denny at CBRE on 9320 0052, 0439 038 005 or andrew.denny@cbre.com.au

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: GROUND FLOOR PREMISES WITH EXCELLENT TERRACE EXPOSURE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Classic waterfront setting in the Old Perth Port precinct of Elizabeth Quay and Barrack Street Jetty. Established passing trade from the Lucky Shag Bar and the South Perth ferry terminal, along with huge increase in traffic since the completion of the new landscaped Bell Tower precinct, and commencement of Perth Water Taxi terminal immediately at the site.

This is the only restaurant site in the precinct with a full 270 degree genuine views including Perth City Skyline, taking in the Elizabeth Quay area, Kings Park profile, the full expanse of Swan River including South Perth foreshore, Heirisson Island and the Burswood complex, as well as Langley Park and East Perth foreshore areas.

*Approx.

101 St Georges Terrace -

4.5 Star NABERS rating

Located in close proximity to the intersection of William Street and St Georges Tce, this property benefits from excellent public transport and retail amenity.

Current Vacancy:

Fully fitted office tenancy incorporating a combination of open plan workstations, meeting rooms and offices.


Ground Floor - Retail or Multiple Uses. 

Tenancies from 250 - 705sqm*.

Access directly off St Georges Terrace.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PRESTIGIOUS CHARACTER BUILDING - OFFICE, RETAIL OR ALTERNATIVE USE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Prime CBD retail tenancies have become available along the busy Hay Street Mall. Join a long list of strong national operators and enjoy maximum exposure and high daily footfall in the heart of Perth.

THE OPPORTUNITIES:

SHOPS 6&7 - CNR OF HAY ST & WILLIAM ST - 134m2*
The location doesn't get much better than this! Corner tenancy with large frontage facing both the Hay St Mall and the busy William St. Fantastic public transport access and only a stone's throw from the Murray Street Mall with Forrest Chase and Raine Square. 

SHOP 3 - HAY STREET MALL - 144m2*
Nestled in the midst of national retailers including T2 Tea, Solid Gold Diamonds, OPSM and Novo Shoes just to name a few, this aptly sized tenancy is ideally suited to a number of uses from service retail to fashion and more.
